# ai-workspace root is local-only — never commit it as an umbrella repo.
# This .gitignore is defense-in-depth: deny everything, then whitelist only the
# workspace meta files and the .claude/ tooling below. The whitelist IS the
# portable skeleton — exactly what gets replicated when you set the workspace up
# in another local runtime; the tiers (repos/active/stable/dormant/archive)
# are machine-local and stay denied by the `*` rule above.

*

# --- root meta files (the skeleton) ---
!.gitignore
!README.md
!AGENTS.md
!CLAUDE.md
!CHANGELOG.md
!VERSION

# The live project index PROJECTS.md is LOCAL-ONLY — it carries private project
# names, status, and blockers, so it is deliberately NOT whitelisted (the `*`
# rule above denies it). Only the sanitized template travels with the skeleton;
# on a fresh workspace: `cp PROJECTS.sample.md PROJECTS.md`.
!PROJECTS.sample.md

# --- read-docs: human/browser guides (docs/) ---
# HANDBOOK.md (workflows), MISSION.html (the workspace's why), DESIGN.docs.md (HTML-doc theme)
!docs/
!docs/**

# --- per-project stencils (templates/) ---
# All *.template.* — copied into new projects by the commands/scripts.
!templates/
!templates/**

# --- workspace tooling (commands, scripts, dashboard generator) ---
!.claude/
!.claude/**

# Generated, local-only dashboard output. The generator scripts stay tracked
# (whitelisted above via .claude/**); the regenerated HTML is not.
.claude/dashboard/dashboard.html
.claude/dashboard/cosmos/

# Python bytecode from the helper scripts — never part of the tracked skeleton.
.claude/**/__pycache__/
